PIX — Web Photo Gallery
=======================

A self-contained web photo gallery.  Upload photos, run one script,
then browse via any web browser.  No database, no framework.


REQUIREMENTS
------------
  - Perl 5.14+  (JSON::PP is a core module; no extra installs)
  - ImageMagick  (provides `convert` and `identify`)
  - A web server with CGI support  (Apache, nginx+fcgiwrap, etc.)


SETUP
-----
1. Copy all pix files into your photos directory:

     pix-init.pl   pix-init.cgi   index.html   pix.js   pix.css

2. Make the scripts executable:

     chmod +x pix-init.pl pix-init.cgi

3. On Apache, ensure the directory allows CGI execution, e.g.:

     Options +ExecCGI
     AddHandler cgi-script .cgi


INITIALIZATION
--------------
Run from the command line (recommended for large collections):

     perl pix-init.pl /path/to/your/gallery

Or let the browser trigger it by visiting:

     http://your-server/gallery/pix-init.cgi

  The web interface shows a live log while photos are processed.
  Once complete it redirects to the gallery automatically.

Re-run pix-init.pl at any time to pick up new or changed photos.
Existing thumbnails are skipped if already up to date.


WHAT GETS GENERATED
--------------------
A  _pix/  directory is created inside the gallery:

    _pix/
      index.json          directory tree + photo metadata
      log.txt             initialization log
      thumb/              150 px thumbnails  (JPEG)
      medium/             800 px images      (JPEG, used in lightbox)
      large/              1600 px images     (JPEG, used for full-screen)

The subdirectory structure of _pix/thumb/ etc. mirrors the source tree.


SUPPORTED FORMATS
-----------------
jpg  jpeg  png  webp  gif   (case-insensitive)
Originals are kept as-is; generated sizes are always JPEG.


BROWSER CONTROLS
----------------
  Click directory card       Enter subdirectory
  Click photo thumbnail      Open lightbox (medium size)
  ‹  ›  buttons              Previous / next photo
  Arrow Left / Right keys    Previous / next photo
  Escape                     Close lightbox
  "Full size ↗"              Open 1600 px version in new tab
  "Download original"        Download the original file
